story.storykicker: WBJEE 2016 result declared: Students can know their results from 4 pm
story.storybody:
The West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations Board (WBJEEB) has announcced the results of the West Bengal Joint Entrance Examination (WBJEE) today, ie June 05, 2016. The students can know their results from 4 pm at the official website, www.wbjeeb.nic.in.

The exam is conducted for admissions into Engineering, Architecture, Pharmaceutical, Medicine etc. courses in various colleges of West Bengal.

To check the results, the candidates should first log on to the official website, the link for which is ww.wbjeeb.nic.in. Next they should click on the live link 'WBJEE Results 2016'. When the new window opens, the candidates should fill in the requisite information such as their roll number, name etc. in the space provided and submit.

The result would show on the screen, the candidates are advised to take a printout of the same for future reference.

The board had successfully conducted the written examination for registered candidates on May 17, 2016 across various cities of West Bengal and in Tripura, Agartala, Assam and Silchar.

The exam was conducted in four subjects: Biological Sciences (100 marks), Mathematics (100 marks), Physics (75 marks) and Chemistry (75 marks).

About WBJEE:

WBJEE is a common entrance examination conducted for taking admission to undergraduate programmes in Medical, Dental, Engineering and Technology, Pharmacy and Architecture in universities, government colleges and self-financed institutes.

For more updates, follow India Today Education.
